### Set Operations
```python
set1 = {1, 2, 3}
set2 = {3, 4, 5}

# Union (all items from both sets)
set1 | set2                 # {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
set1.union(set2)            # Same result

# Intersection (common items)
set1 & set2                 # {3}
set1.intersection(set2)     # Same result

# Symmetric difference (items in either but not both)
set1 ^ set2                 # {1, 2, 4, 5}
```

